(a) this is an express+ejs+socket.io application.
(b) on express routing, always follow this rules:
    - always sanitize any user input received.
    - for database, use mysql.call(procedure name, [argument, list])
    - prefer $.get/$.post approach for template and server interaction (ie: ajax)
- do not suggest any/add any comment to the code.
- suggest code more compact as possible (use less lines).
- do not use camelCase, always name objects as under_case format.
- the following libs already pre-included in index.ejs (main template):
  - moment.js/2.30.1
  - font-awesome/6.4.2
  - jquery@3.7.1
  - @popperjs/core@2.11.8
  - bootstrap@5.3.2
  - bootstrap-icons@1.11.3
  - jquery-validation@1.21.0
  - js-cookie@3.0.5
  - animejs/3.2.2
  - google.com/recaptcha/enterprise.js
  - Chart.js/4.4.1
- use already include js libs when necessary.
- ejs: when possible add linear-gradient/css to buttons/panels, respecting the color theme scheme (darker/lighter).
- always use $ for DOM interaction.
- always apply css respecting the bootstrap color scheme selected.
- never name objects as thisFormat, use this_format for naming convetions.
- never add comments to the code.